    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="89"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 611.37.31/43.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1190.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt on
                    the 11th instant of the Department’s unnumbered instruction of the 2d instant on
                    the subject of the possible modification of the Cuban reciprocity treaty, and to
                    transmit herewith copy of the note which I have to-day handed to the Cuban
                    Secretary of State in compliance therewith. Mr. Sanguily said that he would take
                    the matter up with President Gómez without loss of time and that he would
                    communicate with me further in the course of a few days.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hugh S. Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
